        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 7:28PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 727 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gleneagle, or 13 miles north of Colorado Springs, moving southeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain, wind gusts up to 45 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northwestern Colorado Springs, Monument, Air Force Academy, Black
Forest, and Gleneagle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
